vices, including the Virtual Private Network. Find out more about 2FA and enrolling at https://answers.uillinois.edu/systemoffices/internal/2fa  Virtual Private Network  Securely access UIC resources over a non-UIC Internet connection. While connected to the VPN, your UIC-related data is encrypted.        Host Meetings Online         Host meetings online    Google Meet  Host a conversation, video call, or phone call with up to 250 people at a time, and collaborate on Google documents. Hangouts sync automatically across devices. Users must create a UIC G Suite account to use Google Meet.  Webex Meetings  Host a video and/or audio conference with integrated collaboration tools such as whiteboard, chat, and screen share. While hosts need a Webex account to initiate meetings, participants are not required to have an account.  Zoom  Host a video and/or audio conference with integrated collaboration tools such as whiteboard, chat, and screen share. While hosts need a Zoom account to initiate meetings, participants are not required to have an account.          Use Virtual Collaboration Spaces         Use virtual collaboration spaces    Google Hangouts Chat  From direct messages to group conversations, Chat helps teams collaborate easily and efficiently.  Microsoft Teams  A chat-based workspace and real-time collaboration tool that combines workplace chat, meetings, file storage, and application integration. *MS Teams provides end-to-end security but it is not an approved HIPAA-compliant resource at UIC.          Share Documents Online         Share documents online   Box  Use the Box online file sharing to access documents from any location for collaboration with other University users or external parties on a computer or mobile devices. Request a PHI folder for secure sharing, or a Team folder for online collaboration.  Google Drive  Use Google’s online solution for storing and sharing a variety of documents, from spreadsheets to forms and presentations. Access files on any smartphone, tablet or computer.  OneDrive  Use Microsoft’s online solution for storing, backing up, and sharing documents, allowing easy access to files from any computer or mobile device.        Access Your Email and Calendar         Access your email and calendar   Exchange  Use UIC’s Exchange system to access your email and calendar. Don’t have the Outlook client installed? You can access Outlook on the web at outlook.uic.edu .  Gmail  Visit gmail.uic.edu to access your UIC Gmail email and calendar.        Access Your Voicemail Remotely         Access your voicemail remotely   Voicemail   Remotely access the VoIP Unity voicemail system (Most VoIP users are now on this system)  Remotely access the VoIP Asterisk voicemail system (Some VoIP users are currently still on this system)         Get Help         Get help    Looking for more tools facilitating remote work? Browse our complete list of IT services, tools and resources at accc.uic.edu .  Get answers to the most common questions about online collaboration tools and more in the UIC Answers Knowledge Base at answers.uillinois.edu/uic .  Get Troubleshooting Tips on VPN, Blackboard Learn, software, WiFi, virtual lectures using Collaborate, Zoom or Webex, and more through ACCC’s Guide: go.uic.edu/troubleshooting-tips  Support via email will be available Monday through Friday 9:00am to 5:00pm. We recommend using our Contact Us form , or you can email us at consult@uic.edu.  Phone support will be available on a limited basis Monday through Friday 9:00am to 5:00pm by calling 312-413-0003 option 9 . If you leave a message, a ticket will automatically be created on your behalf and we will follow up with you.                 Support    Back to main content           Academic Continuity    Academic Multimedia Lab and Lightboard Studio    ARC Helpdesk    C-Stop BSB    C-Stop LHS    Daley Library Helpdesk    LTS Support Office                   UIC Logo         Academic  Computing  And  Communications  Center           Q